ere were also very special or dangerous items that had to be fetched in person, or even by large parties of armed librarians.\n\n- Garth Nix, Lirael\n|\nIt is the ability to take a joke, not make one, that proves you have a sense of humor.\n\n- Max\n|\nThe leadership of engagement begins by reconnecting to the physicality and the people of a company, not simply its spreadsheet. It all begins in the workplace.\n\n- Mabel Casey Rex Miller, Change Your Space, Change Your Culture: How Engaging Workspaces Lead to Transformation and Growth\n|\nBe like the sun; warm to everyone, even your enemies.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nAn echo is an imperfect copy of the original, it is information but it is information from a different time and place.\n\n- R.A.Delmonico\n|\nIt seems to me that wherever religion and politics mix in one body, fascist values - and not 'family values' - rear their ugly head.\n\n- Christina Engela, Dead Man's Hammer\n|\nSeek a secret, court danger.Bury a secret, avoid anger.' ~ Angelica Hopes, If I Could Tell You\n\n- Angelica\n|\nI wish I could find MY books listed on GOODREADS - DODGING JOE, THE WOMAN WHO WOULDN'T EXPLAIN, THE BITTER GRAPES - ll available through Amazon and Createspace -\n\n- Saaskia\n|\nIs it shocking?' he asked sarcastically. 'To discover that there are things you don't know?\n\n- Lili Wilkinson, Green Valentine\n|\nThe greater the pressure, the greater the treasure.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nRemember never to text and drive, it's bad grammar, even if you have a deadline. You might cross the line and dead may be your destination. Think about it!!\n\n- Neil\n|\nGreat things often start out small, and only open minds can perceive their inception.\n\n- Innocent Mwatsikesimbe, Mirror\n|\nIf you can lie, you can act, and if you can lie to crazy girlfriends, you can act under pressure.\n\n- Joe\n|\nThere is nothing like a conflict to do the difficult work for you. It is an underrated remedy, cowardly as we are, but it makes everything so much easier.\n\n- J